                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d673">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/6499: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-19T15:00:00-06:00"
                            >December 19, 1929—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:33 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>382. My 377, December 14, 1 p.m.<note n="31" xml:id="d673fn31">Not
                        printed.</note> General Tapia, Chief of the President’s Military Staff,
                    tells me that according to his information <pb facs="0708" n="590"
                        xml:id="pg_590"/> Sandino is endeavoring to purchase a farm near Merida on
                    which to live and that he finds difficulty in securing the purchase money.
                    General Tapia says he has no information whatever that would indicate Sandino is
                    planning to return to Nicaragua.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Nicaragua.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
